WEBVTT

00:05:29.784 --> 00:05:32.272
call themselves "strengths-based."

00:05:32.296 --> 00:05:35.284
The basic idea is that
when we do something unusually well,

00:05:35.308 --> 00:05:37.569
we should focus on learning to repeat it.

00:05:37.593 --> 00:05:41.185
We should play to our strengths
and manage around our weaknesses.

00:05:41.839 --> 00:05:45.340
In his research, Marcus found that one
of the key signs of a great manager

00:05:45.364 --> 00:05:48.688
is a clear focus on recognizing
and developing people's strengths.

00:05:49.267 --> 00:05:52.683
But he's concerned that most of us
don't get to use our strengths enough

00:05:52.707 --> 00:05:53.860
at work.

00:05:53.884 --> 00:05:55.887
MB: Right now, 16, 17
percent of people say

00:05:55.911 --> 00:05:58.403
they have a chance to do
what they do best every day.

00:05:58.427 --> 00:06:01.514
We just finished this 19-country study,
looking at that question.